1.Name: Bulbasaur
1.Entry: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

2.Name: Ivysaur
2.Entry: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

3.Name: Venusaur
3.Entry: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

4.Name: Charmander
4.Entry: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

5.Name: Charmeleon
5.Entry: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.

6.Name: Charizard
6.Entry: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.

7.Name: Squirtle
7.Entry: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

8.Name: Wartortle
8.Entry: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

9.Name: Blastoise
9.Entry: A brutal POKéMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.

10.Name: Caterpie
10.Entry: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

11.Name: Metapod
11.Entry: This POKéMON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

12.Name: Butterfree
12.Entry: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

13.Name: Weedle
13.Entry: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

14.Name: Kakuna
14.Entry: Almost incapable of moving, this POKéMON can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.

15.Name: Beedrill
15.Entry: Flies at high speed and attacks using its large venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.

16.Name: Pidgey
16.Entry: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

17.Name: Pidgeotto
17.Entry: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this POKéMON will fiercely peck at any intruder.

18.Name: Pidgeot
18.Entry: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.

19.Name: Rattata
19.Entry: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

20.Name: Raticate
20.Entry: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

21.Name: Spearow
21.Entry: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

22.Name: Fearow
22.Entry: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

23.Name: Ekans
23.Entry: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

24.Name: Arbok
24.Entry: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.

25.Name: Pikachu
25.Entry: When several of these POKéMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.

26.Name: Raichu
26.Entry: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high voltage power.

27.Name: Sandshrew
27.Entry: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

28.Name: Sandslash
28.Entry: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

29.Name: Nidoran♀
29.Entry: Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKéMON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

30.Name: Nidorina
30.Entry: The female’s horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

31.Name: Nidoqueen
31.Entry: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

32.Name: Nidoran♂
32.Entry: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.

33.Name: Nidorino
33.Entry: An aggressive POKéMON that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

34.Name: Nidoking
34.Entry: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey’s bones.

35.Name: Clefairy
35.Entry: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

36.Name: Clefable
36.Entry: A timid fairy POKéMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

37.Name: Vulpix
37.Entry: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

38.Name: Ninetales
38.Entry: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

39.Name: Jigglypuff
39.Entry: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

40.Name: Wigglytuff
40.Entry: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

41.Name: Zubat
41.Entry: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.

42.Name: Golbat
42.Entry: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

43.Name: Oddish
43.Entry: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

44.Name: Gloom
44.Entry: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn’t drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

45.Name: Vileplume
45.Entry: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

46.Name: Paras
46.Entry: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.

47.Name: Parasect
47.Entry: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

48.Name: Venonat
48.Entry: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.

49.Name: Venomoth
49.Entry: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

50.Name: Diglett
50.Entry: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.

51.Name: Dugtrio
51.Entry: A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

52.Name: Meowth
52.Entry: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

53.Name: Persian
53.Entry: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

54.Name: Psyduck
54.Entry: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.

55.Name: Golduck
55.Entry: Often seen swimming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.

56.Name: Mankey
56.Entry: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

57.Name: Primeape
57.Entry: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

58.Name: Growlithe
58.Entry: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

59.Name: Arcanine
59.Entry: A POKéMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

60.Name: Poliwag
60.Entry: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

61.Name: Poliwhirl
61.Entry: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

62.Name: Poliwrath
62.Entry: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

63.Name: Abra
63.Entry: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.

64.Name: Kadabra
64.Entry: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

65.Name: Alakazam
65.Entry: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

66.Name: Machop
66.Entry: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

67.Name: Machoke
67.Entry: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

68.Name: Machamp
68.Entry: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.

69.Name: Bellsprout
69.Entry: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

70.Name: Weepinbell
70.Entry: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

71.Name: Victreebel
71.Entry: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

72.Name: Tentacool
72.Entry: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

73.Name: Tentacruel
73.Entry: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

74.Name: Geodude
74.Entry: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

75.Name: Graveler
75.Entry: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

76.Name: Golem
76.Entry: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.

77.Name: Ponyta
77.Entry: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

78.Name: Rapidash
78.Entry: Very competitive, this POKéMON will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

79.Name: Slowpoke
79.Entry: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

80.Name: Slowbro
80.Entry: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE’s tail is said to feed on the host’s left over scraps.

81.Name: Magnemite
81.Entry: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.

82.Name: Magneton
82.Entry: Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

83.Name: Farfetch'd
83.Entry: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.

84.Name: Doduo
84.Entry: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.

85.Name: Dodrio
85.Entry: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.

86.Name: Seel
86.Entry: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

87.Name: Dewgong
87.Entry: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

88.Name: Grimer
88.Entry: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

89.Name: Muk
89.Entry: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

90.Name: Shellder
90.Entry: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

91.Name: Cloyster
91.Entry: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

92.Name: Gastly
92.Entry: Almost invisible, this gaseous POKéMON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

93.Name: Haunter
93.Entry: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.

94.Name: Gengar
94.Entry: Under a full moon, this POKéMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.

95.Name: Onix
95.Entry: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.

96.Name: Drowzee
96.Entry: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.

97.Name: Hypno
97.Entry: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.

98.Name: Krabby
98.Entry: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.

99.Name: Kingler
99.Entry: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

100.Name: Voltorb
100.Entry: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKé BALL, they have zapped many people.

101.Name: Electrode
101.Entry: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

102.Name: Exeggcute
102.Entry: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

103.Name: Exeggutor
103.Entry: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

104.Name: Cubone
104.Entry: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKéMON’s real face.

105.Name: Marowak
105.Entry: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

106.Name: Hitmonlee
106.Entry: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.

107.Name: Hitmonchan
107.Entry: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.

108.Name: Lickitung
108.Entry: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon’s. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.

109.Name: Koffing
109.Entry: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.

110.Name: Weezing
110.Entry: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.

111.Name: Rhyhorn
111.Entry: Its massive bones are 1000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying.

112.Name: Rhydon
112.Entry: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.

113.Name: Chansey
113.Entry: A rare and elusive POKéMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.

114.Name: Tangela
114.Entry: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. Its vines shake as it walks.

115.Name: Kangaskhan
115.Entry: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother’s protective pouch until it is 3 years old.

116.Name: Horsea
116.Entry: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

117.Name: Seadra
117.Entry: Capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.

118.Name: Goldeen
118.Entry: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.

119.Name: Seaking
119.Entry: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.

120.Name: Staryu
120.Entry: An enigmatic POKéMON that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.

121.Name: Starmie
121.Entry: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.

122.Name: Mr. Mime
122.Entry: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.

123.Name: Scyther
123.Entry: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.

124.Name: Jynx
124.Entry: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

125.Name: Electabuzz
125.Entry: Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.

126.Name: Magmar
126.Entry: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

127.Name: Pinsir
127.Entry: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.

128.Name: Tauros
128.Entry: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

129.Name: Magikarp
129.Entry: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

130.Name: Gyarados
130.Entry: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

131.Name: Lapras
131.Entry: A POKéMON that has been overhunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.

132.Name: Ditto
132.Entry: Capable of copying an enemy’s genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.

133.Name: Eevee
133.Entry: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.

134.Name: Vaporeon
134.Entry: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

135.Name: Jolteon
135.Entry: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000-volt lightning bolts.

136.Name: Flareon
136.Entry: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

137.Name: Porygon
137.Entry: A POKéMON that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

138.Name: Omanyte
138.Entry: Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.

139.Name: Omastar
139.Entry: A prehistoric POKéMON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.

140.Name: Kabuto
140.Entry: A POKéMON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.

141.Name: Kabutops
141.Entry: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

142.Name: Aerodactyl
142.Entry: A ferocious, prehistoric POKéMON that goes for the enemy’s throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.

143.Name: Snorlax
143.Entry: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

144.Name: Articuno
144.Entry: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

145.Name: Zapdos
145.Entry: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.

146.Name: Moltres
146.Entry: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.

147.Name: Dratini
147.Entry: Long considered a mythical POKéMON until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.

148.Name: Dragonair
148.Entry: A mystical POKéMON that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.

149.Name: Dragonite
149.Entry: An extremely rarely seen marine POKéMON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

150.Name: Mewtwo
150.Entry: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

151.Name: Mew
151.Entry: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.
